Children can be nimble on their feet, especially in a busy area. One moment they are by your side, and the next, they are sprinting to the candy store you forbade them from entering or skipping down the aisle of their favourite toy store. Losing your child in a public area can be a harrowing experience. The most effective precautions are always those that are taken before disaster strikes. Before taking your child out in public, it is advisable to consider some safety measures. Here are a few tips for preventing the loss of your child in shopping centres, amusement parks, beaches, and playgrounds. 